t the\ntwo available BOSS post-reconstructed measurements in Fourier space, once\ncombined with the EFT full-shape analysis, lead to discrepant Hubble parameter\n$H_0$ at $\\sim 0.9\\sigma$. Given the various effects we discuss, we argue that\nthe clustering amplitude $\\sigma_8$ measured with BOSS is not in statistical\ntension with that inferred from Planck under $\\Lambda$CDM.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Aug 2022 17:07:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-12"}
