e theories of\nclassical Diophantine approximation. The dimension results for balls\ngeneralises those obtained in an earlier paper by Hill and the third-named\nauthor for integer matrices to real matrices. In the final section, we discuss\nvarious problems that stem from the results proved in the paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Aug 2022 04:32:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Apr 2023 13:29:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-13"}
